    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Longitudinal shutters or slats built into one side of the swell box of an organ or reed organ, usually with beveled edges and linked together in sets either vertically or horizontally, and pivoted so that the organ player can open or close them as desired by means of the swell action.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Longitudinal shutters or slats built into one side of the swell box of an organ or reed organ, usually with beveled edges and linked together in sets either vertically or horizontally, and pivoted so that the organ player can open or close them as desired by means of the swell action.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Langwerpige luiken of latten die aan één kant van de zwelkast van een orgel of harmonium zijn gebouwd, meestal met schuine hoeken en in sets verticaal of horizontaal met elkaar verbonden, en zo gedraaid dat de orgelspeler ze kan openen of sluiten wanneer hij wil door middel van het zwelkastmechaniek.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052453/Algemene muziekencyclopedie (1961)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>直式檔板或板條，建置於管風琴或簧風琴內增音音箱的某一面，通常其板體呈斜面狀，以直向或橫向排列連結成一排，並以樞軸控制轉動，讓風琴演奏者能透過增音器機械裝置，依需求自行打開或關閉增音器檔板。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Längsverlaufende Jalousie oder Lamelle, die an einer Seite des Schwellkastens einer Orgel oder eines Harmoniums eingebaut ist, gewöhnlich mit abgeschrägten Ecken, in Reihen entweder horizontal oder vertikal verbunden und schwenkbar, sodass der Orgelspieler sie nach Bedarf mit Hilfe der Schwellmechanik öffnen und schließen kann.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
